## ImageJS Feature Explorer

A web demo to upload an image and interactively apply Image-JS methods (filters, transforms, morphology, ROI, etc.) in your browser.

## Installation

git clone https://github.com/your-username/imagejs-feature-explorer.git
cd imagejs-feature-explorer
npm install
npm install image-js
npm run dev

Open http://localhost:3000 in your browser.

## Usage

Upload Image: Click Upload Image and select a file.

Select Feature: Choose a method from the dropdown (grouped by category).

Enter Parameters: If prompted, supply JSON args (e.g. {"radius":2}), or leave blank.

View Result: The processed image appears on the canvas.


## Supported Features

Filters: invert, grey, blur, gaussianBlur, median, gradient, derivative, pixelate, level

Comparison: subtract, and, or, xor, difference

Geometry: rotate, resize, crop, pad, flipX, flipY

Morphology: erode, dilate, open, close, skeleton, topHat, gradient, distanceMap

Operations: threshold, getHistogram, mask, extractChannel, paste, splitChannels

ROI: autoCrop, fromMask, getBoundingBox, cropByROI, clearBorder, fillRoi, invertRoi, roiToMask, extractRoi, projectRoi, paintRoi, sampleRoi, smoothRoi


For full API details, see the Image-JS documentation: https://image-js-docs.pages.dev/
